f=Engineering/quinn/marketplace/eval-harness/SKILL.md · h1:Eval Harness=Eval-driven development (EDD): evals unit tests AI-assisted work. Define expected behavior BEFORE implementation, run continuously, track regressions, measure reliability pass@k. · h2:When to Activate=Setting EDD agent-assisted workflows, Defining pass/fail criteria task completion before work starts, Measuring agent reliability (pass@k) repeated tasks, Creating regression suites prompt/agent/skill changes, Benchmarking behavior across model skill versions · h2:Eval Types=`[CAPABILITY EVAL: <feature>] \· Task: what should be accomplished \· Success Criteria: [ ] criterion 1  [ ] criterion 2  [ ] criterion 3 \· Expected Output: description` · h2:Eval Types=`[REGRESSION EVAL: <feature>] \· Baseline: SHA or checkpoint \· Tests: existing-test-1: PASS/FAIL \· existing-test-2: PASS/FAIL \· Result: X/Y passed (previously Y/Y)` · h2:Eval Types=**Capability evals** system something couldn't before? **Regression evals** change break what worked? · h2:Grader Types=**Code grader** deterministic assertions (grep expected exports, test suite exit code, build exit 0). Preferred wherever possible. **Rule grader** regex/schema constraints outputs. **Model grader** LLM-as-judge rubric (solves problem? structured? edge cases? error handling? score 1–5 reasoning). **Never gates release alone** flaky graders release gates anti-pattern (source) quinn principle. **Human grader** manual adjudication ambiguous outputs; **mandatory security-relevant evals** (route aegis). · h2:Metrics=**pass@1** first-attempt success rate (direct reliability), **pass@3** success within attempts (practical reliability; typical target 90%), **pass^3** runs succeed (stability bar; **1.00 release-critical paths**) · wf=`EVAL REPORT: <feature> \· Capability: 3/3 passed (pass@1: 67%, pass@3: 100%) \· Regression: 3/3 passed (pass^3: 100%) \· Status: READY FOR REVIEW   ← feeds quinn's gate; never self-certifies "SHIP"` · wf=**1. Define (before any work):** capability evals regression evals success thresholds, written eval store. **2. Implement:** work done pass defined evals. **3. Evaluate:** run capability evals (record PASS/FAIL attempt) regression evals (existing suites). **4. Report:** · h2:Eval Storage=`<eval_store>/<feature>.md       # definition \· <eval_store>/<feature>.log      # run history \· <eval_store>/baseline.json      # regression baselines \· <releases>/<version>/eval-summary.md   # release snapshot` · h2:Eval Storage=Configurable business (`quinn-config`): project-local eval store, e.g. Evals versioned code first-class artifacts. · h2:Best Practices=Define evals BEFORE coding (forces clear success criteria) run frequently track pass@k trends over time prefer code graders (deterministic probabilistic) human/aegis review security, never fully automated keep evals fast (slow evals don't get run) version evals code. · h2:Anti-Patterns=Overfitting prompts known eval examples measuring happy paths chasing pass rates while cost/latency drift **flaky graders release gates** treating model-grader score gate evidence own. · b:with other skills=**test-strategy (quinn, custom):** GATE authority tiers, floors, release verdicts. Eval reports evidence gate; skill never issues verdict. Conflicts test-strategy., **regression-map (quinn):** failed evals previously-passing behavior create regression-map entries; fragile areas get standing regression evals., **verification-before-completion (Shared OS):** eval report fresh evidence skill demands "READY REVIEW" without attached run violation both., **charter-enforcement (quinn):** eval runs execute tools follow Rails 1–2 like any run., **aegis:** security-relevant evals (auth, injection, data exposure) require aegis's review; model graders insufficient there., **skill-creator evals (platform):** building/benchmarking VYON skills themselves reuse harness's metrics (pass@k) platform-level usage, method.